headlines.description: — Joel Embiid had 32 points, 13 rebounds and seven assists after an apparent injury scare in the first half and the Philadelphia 76ers beat the Orlando Magic 125-113 on Friday night in a critical game for Eastern Conference playoff seedings.
headlines.shortLinkText: Joel Embiid returns from injury scare, scores 32 as 76ers beat Magic 125-113

headlines.description: — Rookie Adama Sanogo had 22 points and 20 rebounds to shatter his career highs and help the short-handed Chicago Bulls beat the Washington Wizards 129-127 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Rookie Adama Sanogo has 22 points and 20 rebounds to shatter career highs, Bulls top Wizards 129-127

headlines.description: — Payton Prichard scored a career-high 31 points and the Boston Celtics rolled to a 131-98 win over the Charlotte Hornets on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Payton Pritchard scores a career-high 31 points as Celtics rest starters and cruise past Hornets

headlines.description: — Donovan Mitchell scored 33 points, Jarrett Allen had 29 points and 13 rebounds and the Cleveland Cavaliers clinched a playoff berth with a 129-120 victory over the Indiana Pacers on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Donovan Mitchell scores 33 points, Cavaliers clinch playoff spot with 129-120 win over Pacers

events.name: Brooklyn Nets at New York Knicks

headlines.description: — The New York Knicks will be at Madison Square Garden to begin the first round of the playoffs.
headlines.shortLinkText: Knicks top Nets 111-107, earn home-court advantage in 1st round of playoffs and stay alive for No. 2

headlines.description: — When the final whistle blows in Miami on Sunday, the Heat might be in the playoffs. They might also be back in the play-in tournament.
headlines.shortLinkText: Heat never trail on the way to a 125-103 win over Raptors, keeping playoff hope going

events.name: Los Angeles Lakers at Memphis Grizzlies

headlines.description: — LeBron James had 37 points — including six in the final minute — and 10 rebounds, and Anthony Davis had 36 points and 14 rebounds as the Los Angeles Lakers beat the short-handed Memphis Grizzlies 123-120 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: LeBron James scores 37, Anthony Davis finishes with 36 as the Lakers beat Grizzlies 123-120

headlines.description: — Rudy Gobert had 25 points, 19 rebounds and five blocks to help the Minnesota Timberwolves defeat the Atlanta Hawks 109-106 on Friday night and move into a three-way tie for first place in the Western Conference.
headlines.shortLinkText: Rudy Gobert's big night lifts Timberwolves past Hawks and into a first-place tie in the West

events.name: Milwaukee Bucks at Oklahoma City Thunder

headlines.description: — Shai Gilgeous-Alexander scored 23 points and the Oklahoma City Thunder beat the injury-depleted Milwaukee Bucks 125-107 on Friday night to boost their hopes of taking the No. 1 seed in the Western Conference playoffs.
headlines.shortLinkText: Gilgeous-Alexander scores 23 points as the Thunder beat the injury-depleted Bucks 125-107

events.name: Denver Nuggets at San Antonio Spurs

headlines.description: — Devonte’ Graham converted a floater in the lane with 0.9 seconds remaining, and the San Antonio Spurs handed Western Conference-leading Denver a potentially damaging loss, rallying...
headlines.shortLinkText: Devonte' Graham and the Spurs stun the Nuggets, who fall into a three-way tie atop the West

headlines.description: — Rookie Marcus Sasser scored 24 points in his hometown return, including 13 straight Detroit points during a stretch of the third quarter, and the Pistons beat the Dallas Mavericks — playing without Luka Doncic and Kyrie Irving — 107-89 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Marcus Sasser leads Pistons past Mavericks 107-89, with Luka Doncic, Kyrie Irving sitting out

events.name: New Orleans Pelicans at Golden State Warriors

headlines.description: — Stephen Curry and the Golden State Warriors realize they will have a hard road to reach the playoffs.
headlines.shortLinkText: CJ McCollum scores 28 points as Pelicans hold off Warriors 114-109 to help playoff position

events.name: Houston Rockets at Portland Trail Blazers

headlines.description: — Jalen Green had 26 points and the Houston Rockets spoiled Portland's final game at home this season with a 116-107 victory Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jalen Green has 26 points and Houston cruises to 116-107 win over Portland

headlines.description: — Reserve Kenneth Lofton Jr. scored a season-high 27 points and the Utah Jazz beat the Clippers 110-109 on Friday...
headlines.shortLinkText: Jazz beat Clippers 110-109, LA earns home-court advantage for 1st round and locks in 4th seed

headlines.description: — Kevin Durant scored 28 points, Jusuf Nurkic made a late free throw and the Phoenix Suns rallied to beat the Sacramento Kings 108-107 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Kevin Durant scores 28 points, Jusuf Nurkic makes late free throw as Suns beat Kings 108-107
